<% content_for :title, "Terms of Service · Ike" %>
<% content_for :main_class, "max-w-2xl" %>

<article class="text-[15px]">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-1">Terms of Service</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: June 2, 2026</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Thanks for using Ike. Ike is a personal time-tracking tool — a menu-bar app and
    web dashboard for logging how you spend your day across the four Eisenhower
    quadrants. When we say "Ike," "we," "our," or "us," we mean the service at
    <strong>iketimer.com</strong> and its companion macOS app. When we say "you,"
    we mean the person who owns an Ike account.
  </p>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    By using Ike, you're agreeing to these terms. We may update them as the product
    grows; when we make a meaningful change, we'll update the date above and, where
    appropriate, let you know by email. <strong>These terms include a limitation of
    our liability</strong>, so please read them.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Your account</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700 mb-4">
    <li>You sign in with a link we email you — there's no password. You're responsible for keeping access to your email account secure, since anyone with it can sign in as you.</li>
    <li>You must confirm your email address before your account is active.</li>
    <li>You must be a human. Accounts created by bots or automated methods aren't allowed.</li>
    <li>You're responsible for everything that happens under your account.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Acceptable use</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Don't use Ike for anything illegal, abusive, or harmful, and don't try to
    disrupt, attack, or gain unauthorized access to the service or other people's
    accounts. We can suspend or terminate accounts that do.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Your content</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Your time logs and the notes you write are <strong>yours</strong>. You give us
    only the limited permission needed to store and display them back to you so the
    service works. We don't claim ownership of your data, we don't sell it, and we
    don't use it for advertising.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Availability and changes</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Ike is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis, without warranties of
    any kind. It's an independently run product, and we may modify, suspend, or
    discontinue any part of it at any time. We'll try to give reasonable notice
    before any change that would significantly affect you.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Cancellation and termination</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    You can stop using Ike and request deletion of your account at any time by
    emailing us. When an account is deleted, its data is removed from our active
    systems within 30 days and from backups within 60 days; once deleted it can't
    be recovered. We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms or
    put the service or other users at risk.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-8 mb-2">Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    To the fullest extent permitted by law, we won't be liable for any indirect,
